caption.body: Artist and filmmaker Marco Brambilla pays tribute to the golden age of cinema in his reworking of the well-known scene of Gene Kelly and Leslie Caron during the musical finale of the 1951 film, An American in Paris. "Celluloid (An American in Paris, 1951)" by Marco Brambilla, is now playing in the Video Arts Gallery located, pre-security, in the International Terminal.
